<!DOCTYPE task PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Task//EN" "http://docs.oasis-open.org/dita/v1.1/OS/dtd/task.dtd">
<task id="taskId">
    <title>Setting up the workspace</title>
    <shortdesc>Before you can start with the bundlemaker development, you have to checkout all the
        bundlemaker projects and set up your development workspace.</shortdesc>
    <taskbody>
        <prereq>Please make sure that you have installed Java 6, Eclipse 3.6.x or 3.7.x Classic
            (including JDT and PDE tooling) and EGIT on your machine.</prereq>
        <steps>
            <step>
                <cmd>Open the <uicontrol>Git Repositories</uicontrol> View (<uicontrol>Window ->
                        Show View -> Other..., Git -> Git Repositories</uicontrol>).</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Clone the bundlemaker repository:
                        <codeph>git://github.com/wuetherich/bundlemaker.git</codeph>.</cmd>
                <info>In the <uicontrol>Git Repositories</uicontrol> View, you can clone the bundle
                    maker repository by clicking the <uicontrol>Clone a Git Repositories</uicontrol>
                    icon. Enter the repository URL in <uicontrol>Clone Git Repositories
                        Wizard</uicontrol>.<p><image
                            href="./images/dev-getting-started-setup-workspace/import-git-repository-1.png"
                            scale="80"/></p></info>

            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Import the required BundleMaker projects into your workspace</cmd>
                <info>Once the repository is cloned, you can import all required BundleMaker
                    projects into your workspace. <p><image
                            href="./images/dev-getting-started-setup-workspace/import-git-repository-2.png"
                            scale="80"/></p>At least you have to import all the projects that are
                    contained in the <codeph>main</codeph> directory as well as the projects in the
                        <codeph>targetplatform</codeph> directory.<p><image
                            href="./images/dev-getting-started-setup-workspace/import-git-repository-3.png"
                            scale="80"/></p></info>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Set the target platform</cmd>
                <substeps>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>Open the file
                            <codeph>/target.platform/target.platform.target</codeph></cmd>
                        <info><image
                                href="./images/dev-getting-started-setup-workspace/import-git-repository-4.png"
                                scale="80"/></info>
                    </substep>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>Click the <codeph>Set As Target Platform</codeph> in the upper right
                            corner</cmd>
                        <info><image
                                href="./images/dev-getting-started-setup-workspace/import-git-repository-5.png"
                                scale="80"/></info>
                    </substep>
                </substeps>
                <stepresult>After setting the target platform your workspace should not contain any
                    compile errors anymore.</stepresult>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Organize the run configurations</cmd>
                <substeps>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>Open the <i>Organize Favorites...</i> dialog</cmd>
                        <info><image
                                href="./images/dev-getting-started-setup-workspace/Running-BundleMaker-1.png"
                                scale="80"/></info>
                    </substep>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>Select <i>Add...</i> and add all available launch configurations to the
                            favorites list.</cmd>
                        <info><image
                                href="./images/dev-getting-started-setup-workspace/Running-BundleMaker-2.png"
                                scale="80"/></info>
                    </substep>
                </substeps>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Execute the <codeph>BundleMaker UI</codeph> launch configuration</cmd>
                <info><p><image
                            href="./images/dev-getting-started-setup-workspace/Running-BundleMaker-3.png"
                            scale="80"/></p></info>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
</task>
